elements.title: Nikolauskirche
elements.contents: ... that on Christmas Eve in 1818, the Christmas carol "Stille Nacht" ("Silent Night") was first performed in the Nikolauskirche in Oberndorf, Austria?

elements.title: National War Labor Board
elements.contents: ... that the tripartite structure of the National War Labor Board helped the United States keep work stoppages to a minimum during World War II?

elements.title: Willem Lange
elements.contents: ... that on every Christmas Eve since 1994, Willem Lange's story about the fruitcake-delivering farmer Favor Johnson is broadcast on public radio stations in Vermont?

elements.title: Ligue de défense de la race nègre
elements.contents: ... that the anti-colonialist Ligue de défense de la race nègre, which at one point had around 1,000 members, was suppressed by the French government in 1937, ten years after its founding?

elements.title: Mel Bartholomew
elements.contents: ... that Mel Bartholomew, who developed the time-saving square foot gardening method, said that he gardened "with a salad bowl in mind, not a wheelbarrow"?
